Azure Storage provides multiple security features to protect data.

These include:

* Encryption at rest and in transit
* Shared Access Signatures (SAS)
* Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

For example, data is automatically encrypted when stored in Azure.

A real-life use case is secure data sharing using SAS tokens.

Another example is restricting access to storage accounts using RBAC.

Storage security ensures data confidentiality and compliance.
